HEADWORD: Ranal
<hw>Ra"nal</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"n⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having a general affinity to ranunculaceous
plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ranal alliance</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a name
proposed by Lindley for a group of natural orders, including
Ranunculaceae, Magnoliaceae, Papaveraceae, and others related to
them.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

